species group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEE622E067A1E075D84FBEEB89B40AD" blockId="5.[151,1436,1122,1183]" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">
The species of this group are characterized by a short longitudinal keel on male sternum 
<number id="3D997009067A1E0759ACFBEFB9D24049" box="[1215,1232,1123,1147]" pageId="5" pageNumber="306" value="2.0">2</number>
. Due to its close resemblance with 
<taxonomicName id="4C5119AD067A1E075C70FB0BBCE740AD" box="[355,485,1158,1183]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Hoplitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hartliebi">
<emphasis id="B925BE3C067A1E075C70FB0BBCE740AD" box="[355,485,1158,1183]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">H. hartliebi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5119AD067A1E075CE0FB0BBF7640AD" box="[499,628,1158,1183]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Hoplitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albatera">
<emphasis id="B925BE3C067A1E075CE0FB0BBF7640AD" box="[499,628,1158,1183]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">H. albatera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is tentatively assigned to this group although the male is still unknown.
</paragraph>
